---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Portrait from '../components/Portrait.astro';
import Illustration from '../components/Illustration.astro';
import NextSteps from '../components/NextSteps.astro';
import Ticker from '../components/Ticker.astro';

const approachTags = ['Psychodynamic', 'Attachment-Based', 'Relational', 'Depth-Oriented', 'Collaborative'];

const frameworks = [
  {
    name: 'Psychodynamic',
    copy: 'We explore what lives beneath the surface: the patterns, defenses, and relational dynamics that operate outside awareness and shape your inner life.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Attachment-Based',
    copy: 'Your earliest relationships left a blueprint. We look at how that blueprint shows up in how you connect, trust, and protect yourself today.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Relational',
    copy: 'Therapy itself is a relationship. What unfolds between us becomes a live window into the patterns we are working to understand and change together.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Depth-Oriented',
    copy: 'Rather than managing symptoms, we stay curious about what the symptom is protecting. The work goes deeper, and so do the results.',
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Psychodynamic Therapy Approach | Newport Beach & Fullerton"
  description="Psychodynamic, attachment-based therapy in Newport Beach & Fullerton, CA. Understand the 'why' behind your patterns — for lasting change, not quick fixes."
  active="/approach/"
  path="/approach/"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="col">
      <p class="eyebrow">Effective, depth-oriented psychotherapy</p>
      <h1>Explore your past. <br>Own your present. <br><em>Build your future.</em></h1>
      <p>
        We all carry stories that shape how we think, feel, and connect. Deep change happens
        when we honor the full range of our lived experiences and make sense of the narratives
        shaping our lives.
      </p>
      <a class="cta" href="/contact/">Schedule a free consultation <span class="arw">→</span></a>
    </div>
    <Illustration name="depth-approach" size="clamp(380px, 44vw, 520px)" class="hero-figure hero-illustration" />
  </section>

  <Ticker items={approachTags} label="Approach" variant="blue" />

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <section class="section split c-narrow-wide">
    <div class="col gap-20">
      <p class="eyebrow">MY APPROACH</p>
      <h2 class="h2-serif">Connecting deeper,<br><em>living freer.</em></h2>
      <Illustration name="expansion-full" size="260px" color="var(--blue)" class="hero-figure mt-16" />
    </div>
    <div class="prose prose-15">
      <p>We are shaped by the relationships, experiences, and stories that surround us. Some of these stories bring connection and belonging while others leave imprints of pain, shame, or self-doubt. Over time, we develop ways of being with ourselves and others that often reflect our early experiences. Some of these patterns serve us well. Others leave us feeling stuck, disconnected, or unsure of how to move forward. Many of these ways of relating operate outside our awareness, quietly shaping our relationship to ourselves and others in ways we can’t quite grasp. This is where therapy can help.</p>
      <p>Psychodynamic therapy offers a pathway to work through persistent challenges with anxiety, depression, intimacy and closeness, unprocessed loss, patterns of self-sabotage, emotional expression, and beyond.</p>
      <p>Many of the people I work with come to therapy looking for answers to the deep questions about why they’re struggling, or when their best attempts to change on their own aren’t working. While tools can be helpful, they don’t always get to the heart of what’s really going on. My work focuses on meaningful, lasting change. Once you get the deep, personalized support you need to heal and change, everything else changes, too. Using a psychodynamic, depth-oriented approach, we look to understand the “why” behind your feelings and behaviors. Together, we’ll explore how your foundational experiences have shaped your relationships and begin the work of creating new pathways for confidence, connection, and growth.</p>
      <p>The goal is to help you notice the patterns that may be holding you back, understand how they affect your relationships and choices, and free you to inhabit your life in a way that feels truer to who you are and the life you want. By connecting more deeply with your story, your emotions, and the people around you, you can begin to live with a greater sense of freedom, authenticity, and meaning.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quote -->
  <section class="quote-block">
    <Illustration name="relationships-full" size="270px" color="var(--cream)" class="hero-figure" />
    <div class="col gap-28">
      <blockquote>"Not until we are lost do we begin to <em>understand</em> ourselves."</blockquote>
      <cite>Henry David Thoreau</cite>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How I work -->
  <section class="section sage on-color">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div class="stack">
        <p class="eyebrow on-color">HOW I WORK</p>
        <h2 class="serif" style="font-size:48px; line-height:1.1">What shapes how I work with you.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>I work from a psychodynamic framework. Psychodynamic therapy highlights the ways we relate that operate outside our awareness, shaping our relationships with ourselves and others in ways we can’t quite grasp. The goal is to help you notice the patterns that may be holding you back, understand how they affect your relationships and choices, and free you to inhabit your life in a way that feels truer to who you are and the life you want.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ruled-grid cols-2 frameworks" style="margin-bottom:56px">
      {frameworks.map((f) => (
        <div class="ruled-cell">
          <div class="label framework-name">{f.name}</div>
          <p style="color:inherit">{f.copy}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div class="card-row">
      <a class="service-card primary" href="/services/individual-therapy/"><span>Individual therapy</span><span class="arw" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      <a class="service-card secondary" href="/services/couples-therapy/"><span>Couples therapy</span><span class="arw" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:28px; font-size:15px">
      Specialty care: <a class="inline-link" href="/services/premarital-counseling/">premarital counseling</a>, <a class="inline-link" href="/services/therapy-for-anxiety/">therapy for anxiety</a>, and <a class="inline-link" href="/services/therapy-for-creatives/">therapy for creatives</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- What to expect -->
  <section class="section split c-media">
    <Portrait src="/office-photo.jpeg" alt="Nikole's therapy office" placeholder="Office or session photo" accent="bl" />
    <div class="col">
      <p class="eyebrow">What to expect</p>
      <h2 class="h2-serif">Our work <em>together.</em></h2>
      <p class="body">Healing unfolds in its own time. Our work together will honor that rhythm, building trust and welcoming all parts of your experience. I meet each person with highly personalized support, working from the belief that everyone is unique and that healing happens within a safe, genuine, and empathic therapeutic relationship.</p>
      <p class="body">We’ll meet regularly to create a space where both the spoken and unspoken parts of your experience can be understood with curiosity and care. Our work is collaborative: we work together to get to know and understand you, create connections, and discover new possibilities. This is slow, intentional work. It’s about making room for reflection, for growth, and for a deeper sense of self-compassion that honors the complexity of who you are.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/about/">About Nikole <span class="arw">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <NextSteps
    heading="Getting <em>started.</em>"
    copy="If what you’ve read sounds interesting to you, I invite you to reach out. I offer a free 15-minute consultation to give you a chance to ask questions and get a feel for how we might work together."
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Framework cells stack the title above the copy (rather than the shared
     row layout) and color the title with the lime accent. */
  .frameworks .ruled-cell {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .framework-name {
    color: var(--lime);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
